solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minFlipsMonoIncr(String s) {
        int ones = 0, flips = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') ones++;
            else flips = Math.min(flips + 1, ones);
        }
        return flips;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single left-to-right pass counts 1s seen so far and tracks minimum flips needed to make the string monotone. For each 0, either flip it (increment flips) or flip all preceding 1s (use ones).

